<doc id="870195" wikidata="Q1155162" url="?curid=870195" title="Nishikata, Tochigi">
<text>was a town located in Kamitsuga District, Tochigi Prefecture, Japan.

As of 2003, the town had an estimated population of 6,975 and a density of 217.97 persons per km2. The total area was 32.00 km2.

On October 1, 2011, Nishikata was merged into the expanded city of Tochigi. Kamitsuga District was dissolved as a result of this merger.

